### Clerk Modal Configuration

Ensure Clerk modals use the project's theme. In your root layout:

```typescript
import { ClerkProvider } from "@clerk/nextjs";

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <ClerkProvider
      appearance={{
        baseTheme: undefined, // Use default or import from @clerk/themes
        variables: {
          colorPrimary: "hsl(var(--primary))",
          colorBackground: "hsl(var(--background))",
          colorText: "hsl(var(--foreground))",
        },
      }}
    >
      <html lang="en">
        <body>{children}</body>
      </html>
    </ClerkProvider>
  );
}
```

## Component Locations

- All shadcn UI components are in: `src/components/ui/`
- Configuration file: `components.json`
- Components are auto-imported from: `@/components/ui/<component-name>`

## Before You Code - Checklist

Before implementing ANY UI feature:

- [ ] Check if the UI element you need exists in shadcn UI
- [ ] Install the shadcn UI component if not present
- [ ] Use the installed component - DO NOT create custom UI
- [ ] For Clerk auth, use `useClerk()` hooks with shadcn UI buttons
- [ ] For Clerk modals, use `openSignIn()`, `openSignUp()`, `openUserProfile()`
- [ ] Customize using shadcn UI's variants, not custom components

